detaileddescription.para: majorTicks can be set any locator available. By default, the majorTicks locator is an AutoLocator with density set to 50 (pixels/tick).
This property will also automatically create locators based on primitive inputs. For example: ... majorTicks:5 ... will create a SpacedLocator at intervals of 5,
... majorTicks:[0,5,10,20] ... will create a HardLocator at the locations provided in the list.
... majorTicks:null ... will set the Locator back to the default AutoLocator.
Reading this property will return the list of locations at that time (not the Locator object, itself!)
